    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">SRM Console</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">At the <text styleclass="Code Example">&gt;&gt;&gt;</text> prompt the console accepts <text styleclass="Code Example">show</text> and <text styleclass="Code Example">set</text> commands plus device and diagnostic commands; variable changes persist to the flash / NVRAM image. This subsection covers the console and its everyday commands.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">In this section</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">SRM Overview -- what the console is and its reported versions.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Common Commands -- the command set at a glance.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">show config -- the system configuration table.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">show device -- enumerated devices.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">show memory -- the memory array.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">boot -- bootstrap (planned; HALT today).</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">set -- change and persist a console variable.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">SRM Environment Variables -- where the full variable list lives.</li>
    </list>
